For those of you who thought this was too greasy. I liked this recipe but also thought it was a little on the greasy side too sooo... I cut the bacon fat to 1tb, thickened it up with about 1tb of flour and added a cup and a half of chicken broth,added the beans simmered until it got a little viscosity and there you go. I've also tried blanching as someone else suggested and also "stir frying" the beans with a little of the bacon grease, sesame oil works well too if you want to cut more fat, just use a little grease in the sauce, it gives good flavor. It's all good!!

