Rating: 3
We made it three times over the holidays. Twice I used fresh, triple-washed spinach and made it in advance. With the spinach it was much faster as there was no preparation for the spinach. It looked it very elegant on the plate and our guests loved it. I micro-waved the bacon while sauteeing the shallots, then added the bacon fat to the pan. I added the bacon to the pan here also, which worked the first time but not the second time (see below). I then removed the pan from the burner and stirred the spinach (a bag and a half or more for twelve) in batches in the pan to cover it with the mixture. I packed it in a large glass bowl sprinkling each batch with salt, covered tightly with plastic wrap and refrigerated it. Just before serving, I micro-waved it (still covered with the plastic and watching carefully so as not to shrink the spinach too much) for a couple of minutes. That's it! It was great to have so little mess and effort needed at serving time! [Adding the bacon before refrigerating worked the first time because I only refrigerated it for about an hour or less. The second time, I left it in the refrigerator several hours and the bacon got mushy. Next time, I'll leave it at room temperature until just before or just after micro-waving.]

Rating: 4
Excellent flavor and so easy! I thought it had just the right amount of "grease" and the combination of bacon and caramelized shallots was just wonderful. I can't imagine why other reviewers thought this was too much trouble for weeknight - simply slice the shallots, cook the bacon and shallots, steam the green beans, mix it all together and POOF! You're done!

