WOW! OK, I admit, I usually dislike those folks who change a recipe, and then review it, and now I'm doing it! I took a large bag of frozen whole green beans and adjusted the amount of bacon to match, and used a chopped onion in place of the shallots (none in the house), but otherwise followed the recipe as written. My husband was eating them as I cooked, and I barely got them onto the platter! My seven year old ate three servings, and picked the serving platter clean. This is now a staple at our house. (I cooked the beans early in the day, and kept in the fridge) I had no problems with the greasiness mentioned by other reviewers, but my bacon didn't leave a lot of drippings (I used Oscar Meyer center cut), and I actually needed to add the butter to have enough to saute the beans in.

